  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "This model has been applied in clinical research contexts involving Class III ventricular assist devices. The CFD hemolysis prediction framework for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump was assessed under ASME V&V 40 at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all operating conditions. Seven of thirteen credibility factors were formally assessed; six remain flagged as epistemic gaps. All assessed factors achieved levels meeting or exceeding required thresholds under the Minimal profile review. The assessment team concluded that the model provides sufficient credibility for the intended application based on available evidence.",
